 off-axis viewing angle or significant substructure in the\nemission region. Simultaneous multi-hour broadband radio observations of future\nGRB afterglows will allow us to characterize the scintillation more completely,\nand hence to probe the observer viewing angle, the evolution of the jet Lorentz\nfactor, the structure of the afterglow emission regions, and ISM turbulence at\nhigh Galactic latitudes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 20 Jun 2018 23:09:12 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 10 Jan 2019 00:15:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-01-16"}
